  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-2" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">About the work</h2>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Why the work is being done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NILGOSC is committed to the implementation of an EDRMS not only to improve efficiency and effectiveness across the organisation, but also importantly to comply with legislation and fully implement electronic retention and disposal of corporate records.  SharePoint has records management functionality and, as it is a Microsoft application, it is familiar to staff and can be fully integrated with email and other applications currently in use. Therefore, SharePoint is the preferred option as a platform to develop an EDRMS. <br><br>This pilot, which will be conducted with IT and Governance records only, is the Alpha Phase of the project and will be used to test how the system will work, prior to rollout to the wider business.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Problem to be solved
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NILGOSC is seeking a supplier to provide tailored, flexible training to the project team, to assist with the development of a SharePoint Online EDRMS solution, in line with its Retention &amp; Disposal Schedule. This is a pilot phase, which will involve a subset of corporate records. The focus of the partnership will be to provide training on specific areas of SharePoint Online, with the NILGOSC project team providing operational control. These training areas will include, SharePoint Admin Centre, document stores and site collection settings, retention tagging and labelling of documents, managed metadata, terms store, retention and security policy settings, IRM etc. There will also be a requirement to assist with the development of a workable search and retrieval function, within the EDRMS. <br>By the end of the Alpha phase, NILGOSC will have developed a SharePoint EDRMS, that will facilitate the automated retention and disposal of corporate records, which can then be further developed using the training provided for Beta and Live phases.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Who the users are and what they need to do
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          All NILGOSC staff need to be able to access and manage records easily, while ensuring that electronic records are retained and disposed of in line with NILGOSC’s Retention &amp; Disposal Schedule.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Early market engagement
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Previously, NILGOSC had sought a supplier to deliver the entire Alpha phase. Including, design, creation, and testing. Due to their resourcing issues and the acquirement of an internal member of staff within NILGOSC with experience of EDRMS, a decision was taken to change the approach for this project. This has led NILGOSC to seek a training partner, with the design, creation and testing brought in-house.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Any work that’s already been done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NILGOSC are running an on-premise Microsoft SharePoint 2016 farm on a Hyper V environment. Microsoft Windows Server 2012 R2 &amp; Microsoft SQL Standard 2017. The SharePoint Database is approximately 3.7TB. This is a core system that holds all NILGOSC’s member records and is accessed daily by staff.<br><br>NILGOSC also currently utilise Microsoft 365 through the E3 licence for Exchange Online and Microsoft Teams.<br><br>Discovery phase confirmed SharePoint Online as a feasible &amp; preferred option for the implementation of effective corporate records management and disposal.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Existing team
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NILGOCS&#39;s project team consists of the IT and Governance departments, with the project being led by the Governance Manager.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Current phase
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Alpha
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-3" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Work setup</h2>
  
  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Address where the work will take place
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Templeton House, 411 Holywood Road, Belfast, BT4 2LP<br>The provider will be expected to work on site for face to face meetings.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Working arrangements
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The alpha team will be a cross functional, multi-disciplinary team that will embrace Agile principles in order to develop SharePoint online so it can be an effective records management solution for NILGOSC. The provider will work in a collaborative and transparent way with the NILGOSC project team and will provide targeted training and development sessions.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
